Three suspected kidnappers have been arrested by vigilantes along Ochadamu-Itobe-Lokoja Road, Kogi State.The alleged kidnappers, who had reportedly been terrorising the state, were arrested on Sunday by the vigilante members from Ochadamu and Ejule communities. The alleged kidnappers were said to have come to the highway but were intercepted by the vigilantes.The suspects were said to have confessed and revealed their mode of operation, the nature of weapons they used, and the names of other gang members.“Another successful operation against the kidnappers along Ochadamu, Itobe Lokoja Road yesterday, with the arrest of three kidnappers by the combined team of local vigilantes from Ochadamu and Ejule,” one of the operatives told SaharaReporters on Monday.